title.narrative: 1.1 EVIDENCE-BASED, GENDER-RESPONSIVE EDUCATION & YOUTH REFORM POLICIES

description.narrative: Policymakers and key stakeholders have coordinated and developed evidence-based, gender-responsive education and youth-reform policies., which contributes to Access To Quality Learning Opportunities, Access To Quality Learning Opportunities (Covid), Equitable Access To Quality Education, Learning, Skills, Participation And Engagement. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Partnerships And Engagement: Public And Private, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2022, more Palestinian children and adolescents, especially the most vulnerable, benefit from improved access to quality and inclusive learning opportunities in safe and protected environments and are better able to contribute to their community and national development

description.narrative: UNICEF provided technical support to MoE to develop a roadmap for STEM approaches through a national consultative workshop and agreed on five pillars. With UNICEF support, an assessment of volunteerism in Palestine has been completed and the findings were used to develop a national framework for national youth volunteering programme under the Prime Minister’s Office. UNICEF responded to the humanitarian needs of the children in Gaza through provision of stationery kits to over 74,000 children, provision of recreational summer activities to over 55,000 to support their MHPSS, trained over 13,000 teachers on psychological first aid and rehabilitated 20 damaged schools. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:20/01/2022
